message.content: The most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is "cs.CL" (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and question answering. Other likely sub-categories could include "cs.IR" (Information Retrieval) as the dataset was obtained by crawling forums, "cs.AI" (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves building QA systems, "cs.LG" (Machine Learning) as it involves learning representations of the IT domain language, and "cs.CY" (Computers and Society) as it deals with real-world issues in the automated customer support domain.
